  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/61732387" />
    <a title="Lewis Weinstein" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2231715-lewis-weinstein"><img alt="Lewis Weinstein" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442501879p2/2231715.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/61732387?book_show_action=true">Jul 01, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lewis Weinstein" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lewis Weinstein" href="/user/show/2231715-lewis-weinstein">Lewis Weinstein</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2231715-lewis-weinstein?shelf=crime-and-thrillers">crime-and-thrillers</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer61732387" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13088745537260772181">I am a real fan of Elizabeth George&apos;s novels, and am very hopeful, as I begin Careless in Red, that she has regained the touch she lost so badly in What Came Before He Shot Her.<br/><br/>I&apos;m about 400 pages in, and very pleased. The plotting is meticulous, as always with George. There were enough characters that I made a list; I guess if I did that, perhaps she should have. <br/><br/>There is a very touching process going on in this book. Thomas Lynley, who George has &quot;lived with&quot; through 14 other novels, has been </span>
  <span id="freeText13088745537260772181" style="display:none">I am a real fan of Elizabeth George's novels, and am very hopeful, as I begin Careless in Red, that she has regained the touch she lost so badly in What Came Before He Shot Her.<br /><br />I'm about 400 pages in, and very pleased. The plotting is meticulous, as always with George. There were enough characters that I made a list; I guess if I did that, perhaps she should have. <br /><br />There is a very touching process going on in this book. Thomas Lynley, who George has "lived with" through 14 other novels, has been devastated by the murder of his wife Helen (two books ago). George is carefully and tenderly nursing her character back to life. It's nice to watch, as an important sub-plot to the solution of the current crime. Or maybe it's the main plot.<br /><br />Finished. It's a long book, which allowed me to savor the plot and the characters. The ending was unusual (I won't say what, of course) but George shows she's willing to take risks in her writing, and she pulls it off. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13088745537260772181" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


