<div id="review_38657482" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/38657482" />
    <a title="patience" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1464954-patience"><img alt="patience" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1334360038p2/1464954.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/38657482?book_show_action=true">Nov 25, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="patience" class="user" itemprop="url" name="patience" href="/user/show/1464954-patience">patience</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">mystery fans</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer38657482" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4261803241181650063">One of my problems with Elizabeth George is that she writes books with so many characters it&apos;s hard for me to establish who is who at first. Also, as with so many other writers, she has put her characters through so many horrible personal tragedies she almost seems like a sadist. It&apos;s similar to a tv show that has been running for so long the writers feel they must shoot the main character, or his wife, or his best friend, or his mother...to keep things interesting...even if it&apos;s supposedly a bo</span>
  <span id="freeText4261803241181650063" style="display:none">One of my problems with Elizabeth George is that she writes books with so many characters it's hard for me to establish who is who at first. Also, as with so many other writers, she has put her characters through so many horrible personal tragedies she almost seems like a sadist. It's similar to a tv show that has been running for so long the writers feel they must shoot the main character, or his wife, or his best friend, or his mother...to keep things interesting...even if it's supposedly a book about doctors who work in a hospital. It beggars belief. Still, this was pretty good, even if it could've been improved with editing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4261803241181650063" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

